## What is E5 Enclave?

E5 Enclave Incorporated is a 501(c)(3) Lineage-based Think Tank — a publication of record, a coordinating institution, and a Coalition of the Willing. We convene Black-led organizations, individual builders, partner institutions, and aligned coalitions to repair, rise, and govern the lineage's future.

Founded Juneteenth, MMXXVI, in Liberty City, Florida. EIN: 99-3822441.

## What is FarmBlock?

[FarmBlock](/programs/lineage-farms/) is the blockchain-anchored governance layer of our flagship Environmental program, *Lineage Farms*. It pairs cooperative urban agriculture with a transparent, member-governed ledger — every contribution recorded, every distribution rule member-authored, every audit interface open to the membership.

## What is Restitution 246?

[Restitution 246](/restitution-246/) is the Enclave's lead campaign under the Emancipated pillar — a disciplined wage-loss and opportunity-loss framework for the 246 years of stolen labor under American chattel slavery. Anchored to the Craemer (2015) wage-hour methodology and the Lloyd Kelly framework. R246 is *one disciplined lane* of the larger reparations question; it does not claim to settle the whole.

## How does the Coalition work?

The Coalition follows a **33/17/50** model: 33% institutional members (Black-led organizations), 17% individual builders, and 50% reserved seats for partner institutions and aligned coalitions. Member organizations remain *sovereign* — we coordinate, we do not absorb. [Read more about the Coalition →](/coalition/)

## How can I support the work?

- **Donate** to the founding fund: [/donate/](/donate/)
- **Apply** to the Coalition: [/coalition/apply/](/coalition/apply/)
- **Buy** through the store: [/store/](/store/) (proceeds support programs)
- **Partner** as an institution or coalition: [/contact/](/contact/)
- **Cite** our records in your work — and keep us honest

## Are donations tax-deductible?

E5 Enclave Incorporated is a 501(c)(3) public charitable organization (EIN: 99-3822441). Donations made through our official channels are generally tax-deductible to the extent permitted by law. Please consult your tax advisor for guidance specific to your situation. We provide donation receipts for tax purposes.

## How do I join a program?

Each [program page](/coalition/) names its own application path. The fastest single point of entry is the [Coalition application](/coalition/apply/) — note in the message which program(s) you're interested in (McCartney Academy, Lineage Farms · FarmBlock, Block to the Boardroom).

## How do I get on the press list?

For interview requests, citations, and substantive coverage, write [press@e5enclave.com](mailto:press@e5enclave.com). The full [press kit](/press/) lives at /press/.

## How do organizations partner with E5?

Black-led organizations apply to the Coalition through the [application form](/coalition/apply/). Partner institutions, foundations, and aligned coalitions reach out via [contact@e5enclave.com](mailto:contact@e5enclave.com) — we route to the right desk and respond within five business days.

## Where can I read the founding documents?

The three founding documents — *Parallel Negros*, *Measure the Wound*, and *Restitution 246* — are published on the Enclave's reading surface and indexed in [The Record](/record/).

